          <td bgcolor="" valign="top" width="1"><img src="/lotr/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="0" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/blu_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Longshot in Santa Rosa, CA 2/9/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.90)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5711'>Michael "Longshot" Mendoza</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5711&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> February 16, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> This is actually 2 reports, the 1st one being a normal Swiss in Santa Rosa (north of San Francisco) and the 2nd being an uncommon/common only tourney in Cupertino (south of SF).  Yeah, uncommon/common only sounds hokey, and it was, but I&#39;ll get to that.  I meet up with Ray Liu for the Santa Rosa tourney and we have 8 players, including John Miller, the TD at Clark&#39;s Cards.  I was using my old Gandalf archery deck and Nazgul anti-archery deck.  I bid 3-5, starting Green Dragon Inn to get Sam and also start Gandalf.  This tourney was 5 rounds.<br>
<br>
Game 1 v Ray Liu (starts Arwen & Sam & Prancing Pony) (uses Uruk/Nazgul)<br>
I knew with only 8 people I would have to play Ray sooner or later, might as well get it out of the way now.  He knows my start so he bids 5 to my 4 and goes 1st.  He pulls Aragorn and uses Sam to get back to 3 burdens.  He moves, and I play Nelya and get my site 1 out.  Nelya wounds Arwen & Aragorn, he stops.  I figured I needed Sam to remove burdens, & I figured I&#39;d draw Aragorn no prob with 4 copies.  I couldn&#39;t have been more wrong.  I pull Sam and move, he plays a Troop of Uruks and Gandalf takes 2, I stop.  He plays Boromir and Pippin & Gwemegil, so I play Enquea and another Nazgul and exert Enquea twice to kill Arwen.  Then Aragorn and Boromir each take 2 wounds.  I play Legolas and move to 3, he has nothing.  He plays Greenleaf & moves to Moria Lake, I play King w/Blade who he kills w/archery (I play All Blades perish to make him exhaust his archers).  He moves again, I play 2 Nazgul and Relentless Charge (Aragorn & Lego die), Pippin & Sam die to 1 Nazgul while Boromir takes 2 wounds from the other at site 5.   So he has exhausted Boromir & healthy Frodo left.  I move to site 4, he plays an Uruk, I stop.  He plays Thrarin, I play a fierce Nazgul at site 6, kill Thrarin & Boromir.  I move to 5, he plays Lurtz & Troop, but I kill them w/Strength of Spirit arcehery damage & a couple PATHS.  Then he moves a lone Frodo to site 7, and says &quot;Do you have a Nazgul?&quot;  I said &quot;Yeah, you give me 8, right?&quot;  He says &quot;Yeah, thats game.&quot;  But he only gives me 7 pool really, and he scoops up his cards, then 5 minutes later he just realizes he only gave me 7 pool, and it turns out he would&#39;ve lived since I only had Witch-king in hand.  So there&#39;s a lesson, don&#39;t scoop up a game!  Win +3 (3).<br>
<br>
Best: Killing 6 companions.<br>
Worst: Neither of us realizing the pool was actually 7, not 8.  For some odd reason we both thought site 7 added 7 to the pool.<br>
<br>
Game 2 v Sean Cabin (Arwen & Legolas) (uses Nazgul)<br>
He bids 0, I go 1st.  I pull Sam, remove my 3 burdens, move to Weatherhills where he plays Breath & Cantea, wounding Gandalf twice & Breathing on him.  He plays Aragorn, Elven bow on Arwen, moves, I play 2 Nazgul, Arwen & Aragorn each take 2 wounds.  My hand is full of Nazgul, I&#39;m trying to draw fellowship cards, but I can only move to the Ford, where he plays Nelya (free) & Morgul Gates to bring in Ostea for 2.  He makes Ostea fierce, & I only have Frodo, Sam, & Gandalf.  Gandalf blocks Nelya twice but Sam & frodo die to Ostea.  I suck.<br>
<br>
Best:  None at all<br>
Worst:  My only fellowship cards were Aragorn&#39;s possessions & Arwen&#39;s sword, no Servants or PATHS.<br>
<br>
Game 3 v Mason Gilligan (R-Boromir & C-Merry) (uses Uruks)<br>
Mason&#39;s a cool guy, I loaned him some cards until his cards came in.  He bids 0, I go 1st.  I play Greenleaf, pull Sam, remove my 3 burdens, move to Trollshaw Forest.  He plays an Uruk Guard, Greenleaf exerts twice to kill it.  I move again, he has nothing.  Now he just moves, I drop Nelya to get my sites 2 & 3 out, Boromir takes 2 wounds.  He stops, and I move to 4, he plays nothing, so I move again and he drops a squad on me.  Luckily I had servants and PATHS to survive without anyone dying.  It was Lurtz and 3 scrubby minions, nothing I couldn&#39;t handle.  He moves to site 3 and stops when I play a Nazgul, then I move and from here on ARV saves me from having to stop.  I&#39;m drawing my Strength of Spirits to do archery too, so I&#39;m good to go from 5-7, then from 7-9.  It didn&#39;t really matter what he had, I just had all the cards to kill anything.  Win +3 (7).<br>
<br>
Best: My deck just worked great.<br>
Worst: Beating a friend.<br>
<br>
Game 4 v Jason Piazza (Arwen & Greenleaf) (uses Nazgul)<br>
He bids 0, I go 1st.   I play Sam, remove burdens, play Arwen and her sword (good luck there), move.  He was minion screwed outta the gate, with nothing to stop me.  I move to 3.  He plays Boromir & Aragorn w/bow and blades on both, moves and I play 3 fierce Nazgul (2 relentless charges in hand).  He exhausts his archers to kill 2 of them, Arwen & Boromir each take a wound to the 3rd.  He moves again, I play Not Easily Destroyed, saving 5.  He plays ARV, so I remove 3 to heal Nelya (the only Nazgul out), play Relentless Charge to kill his archers, then heal Nelya again.  Then I wound Arwen & Boromir once each.  After that I move to site 4, he has nothing, I move to 5, he plays 1 Nazgul which Arwen eats up.  He plays Arwen&#39;s sword, moves to 4, I play Cantea & Morgul Gates to bring in Ostea w/sword.  Boromir loses his sword to cantea & takes 2 wounds, Arwen beats on Ostea.  He stops.  I move to 6, he plays Nelya, who dies to Arwen, I move again, he has Witchking, but I have ARV & PATHS.  I&#39;ve nevre moved so easily against Nazgul.  The next turn he moves to 5, and stops, I play Aragorn and move to 8, he plays 2 nazgul, I stop.  Then he moves to 6 and I move to 9 and win, no one dies.  Win +3 (10).<br>
<br>
Best: Early beating on his archers.<br>
Worst: He got minion screwed early.<br>
<br>
Game 5 v John Miller (R-Gimli & Greenleaf & East Road) (uses Uruks)<br>
He bids 3 & wins the toss, so he goes 1st.  He plays Gimli&#39;s Helm & Moves, I play Nelya for 2 (using Morgul Gates), play Not Easily Destroyed, get my site 1 out & remove 3 to heal Nelya.  Nelya takes an archery damage & Gimil does a cleaving blow & exerts twice to cleave Nelya.  He moves again, I play Cantea & Relentless Charge wounding Lego.  So Legolas takes another wound in skirmish, & Gimli dies to the fierce skirmish.  I pull Sam, remove burdens & play Aragorn w/bow.  I move, he plays Troop of Uruks so I play 2 Strength of Spirits & 2 PATHS to kill it.  I move again, he has nothing.   He plays R-Boromir, moves to my Moria Lake, I play Ostea (make himself fierce) & Cantea & Relentless Charge.  Legolas skirmishes Ostea, dying the 2nd time, Boromir takes 2 wounds.  I move to site 4, he plays Saruman&#39;s Ambition, I stop.  He plays Sting (uses it), moves to 5, I play Ostea w/Nazgul Sword & a Tip.  So Boromir dies & Frodo takes 1 wound & 2 burdens & a Tip (Nelya is Dmg +1).  I move to 5, he plays Lurtz & an Orthanc Assassin & Spies of Saruman, so ARagorn (he has Armor) takes 2 wounds from Lurtz and Gandalf takes 2 from the Assassin, I stop.  He moves to site 6, I play Morgul Gates & Nelya for 3, Frodo takes a wound (he&#39;s now exhausted) & then 2 burdens (8 burdens now).  i move to 6 and stop.  He heals & moves to site 7 (9 burdens now, remember Frodo is still Tipped).  I do nothing (I want to corrupt Frodo), then i move to site 7 and play Verstatility & use PATHS to kill his Troop & Assassin.  Then on his turn the Tip adds the 10th burden and Frodo crosses to the dark side.  Win +3 (13).<br>
<br>
Best: Corruption win for the 1st time and with a Tip to boot!<br>
Worst: Not much really.<br>
<br>
So I end up 4-1, as does Jason Piazza.  We don&#39;t bother with opposition totals, we go for the final confrontation.  The game was really a repeat of game 4, but he was much closer this time.  He was at site 7 when I hit 9.  So I get 1st, and I win 18 packs, Jason gets like 8 packs and Ray Liu gets 3rd and 4-5 packs.  Ray puled Lurtz, Aragorn, & the rare Ring, all I pulled was a Greenleaf (yes, he&#39;s good, but the other 17 packs stunk BAD).  I hang around for some trades and Ray and I head off back to SF.  Thanks for reading.<br>
<br>
Props to:<br>
John Miller for running the tourney nicely.<br>
Sean for the tough 2nd game.<br>
Jason & Ray for doing well.<br>
Everyone who read this, & liked it.<br>
<br>
Slops to:<br>
Jeff Grein, Chris Schoenthal, & Chris Dejong, where were y&#39;all?<br>
Golden Gate Bridge toll being $3?  What happened to $2?<br>
<br>
That night I quickly build an Uruk deck with all kinds of different fellowship stuff for the uncommon/common tourney.  I meet Steve Daniel for that one, and we go.  I&#39;ll go through these games quick since uncommon/common format sucks bad, and most of you won&#39;t play it, but there are good tips to know.  There are 8 players and Jeff Grein is the TD at Superstars.<br>
<br>
Game 1 v Mike Robert (same deck as mine)<br>
I go first with the Green Dragon to pull Sam and remove my burdens.  I get Aragorn w/sword and Armor out and move to 2.  Aragorn w/sword is HUGE here.  After that we each double move but he stops at site 6, I move on and win.  3 points<br>
<br>
Game 2 v Macius Kincinski (elf archery/Nazgul)<br>
This is a huge deck also.  The elves beat down (the ally archers too).  The tips & breaths combined w/Lemenya are huge too.  I only won because I went first, and at site 9 I lost everyone but Frodo.  Win.  6 points<br>
<br>
Game 3 v Chris Larkin (same as Macius)<br>
Same game as against Macius, except EVERYONE died at site 9, he had Ostea to make Lemenya fierce, and with his sword he&#39;s like a poor man&#39;s Witchking with Blade.  Lose.  7 points<br>
<br>
Game 4 v Gary Williams (Moria & various fellowship)<br>
As in all my games, I go first.  But he was really able to stop me every turn.  He always had fellowship when he needed it, and Shadow when he needed that.  I notice at site 8 he&#39;s discarding half his hand during regroup.  Apparently he thought you could discard as much as you wanted.  I&#39;m at 8, he&#39;s at 7, its his turn.  He moves to 8, I play 3 uruks to his Aragorn, Gandalf, Frodo.  He has the Mysterious Wizard & Swordarm to kill the 2 uruks and Frodo takes 2 wounds.  Then he plays Gondor&#39;s vengence to kill the last uruk and moves again to 9, I only have 3 uruk to play so Frodo takes 2 burdens and lives.  That sucks.  Lose.  8 points.<br>
<br>
So Chris and Macius and Steve Daniel take 1st, 2nd, 3rd, in that order.  I get 4th by opposition totals (woohoo!).  Notice the 2 elf/Nazgul decks won.  But i think if they had faced Moria decks their elves wouldn&#39;t have done so well.  Scouts soak up archery and wallcrawlers kill it altogether (at least in this uncommon/common format).  Technically this shouldn&#39;t be sanctioned, but I guess no one&#39;s telling Decipher, heheh.  Thanks for reading, and thanks to Jeff for running the tourney. <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3378&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
